Governor Perdue:

I hope you will not sign this bill in the interest of crime victims who want justice and punishment for the heinous crime of murder and for our citizens who will have to pay millions to handle the appeals from death row and statisticans hired for courtrooms across the state.  Public safety is also a consideration as we cannot know when some of these murderers could be released.

